                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d282">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 PW/3–2746: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smyth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="58" xml:id="d282fn58">Repeated by the Department to the Embassy in the
                        Soviet Union in telegram No. 590, March 80, 1 p.m.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-27T15:00:00+07:00"
                            >March 27, 1946—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>577. This afternoon Vice Minister [for] Foreign Affairs Liu Chieh informed me
                    that Foreign Office replied today to Soviet Ambassador’s note (see Embassy’s 552
                    March 23), stating that Chinese Govt, agreed to date, end of April, for
                    withdrawal Soviet forces from Manchuria, but requesting that Soviet Govt,
                    furnish definite schedule of Soviet troop withdrawals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smyth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
